# Observability

Two complementary tools. Use both.

## MLflow — experiments & aggregate metrics

One **run** per evaluation execution (dataset × judge set × model config).

- Log params (via `observability.run_metadata`): `run_id`,
  `dataset_fingerprint`, `rubric_version_<pillar>`, `prompt_version_<pillar>`,
  `model_alias`, `model_version`, `kb_version`, `run_config_hash`.
- Log per-pillar metrics (see `docs/METRICS.md`): `exact_match_rate`,
  `within_1_rate`, `off_by_2_rate`, `off_by_3_plus_rate`,
  `mean_absolute_error`, `weighted_kappa`, `spearman_correlation`,
  `severity_aware_alignment`.
- Log run-level metrics: `total_rows`, `rows_successfully_scored`,
  `rows_failed_parsing`, `avg_latency_ms_<pillar>`, `tokens_in_<pillar>`,
  `tokens_out_<pillar>`, `cost_estimate_<pillar>`.
- Log artifacts: resolved configs, per-row results parquet,
  confusion matrices, score distributions, failure-tag distributions.

## Langfuse — per-row traces

- One **trace** per `(record_id, run_id)`.
- One **span** per judge call with input prompt, raw + parsed output,
  tokens, latency, cost, model fingerprint, `prompt_version`,
  `rubric_version`.
- Link MLflow `run_id` in trace metadata; link Langfuse trace URL from the
  per-row results table in the dashboard.

## Hard rules

- API keys from env only. Never from configs or code.
- PII redaction via `observability.redaction` when
  `observability.redact_pii: true` in config.
- **Observability failures MUST NOT break a run.** Wrap writes in try/except,
  log a single warning per failure type, keep processing rows.
- Runners (`orchestration/runner.py`) own MLflow run lifecycle and Langfuse
  trace creation. Judges receive the span handle via `RunContext` and only
  add attributes — they never create traces themselves.
